title: Keys and Rooms
content: There are rooms and you start in room 0. Each room has a distinct number in , and each room may have some keys to access the next room. Formally, each room has a list of keys , and each key is an integer in where . A key opens the room with number . Initially, all the rooms start locked (except for room 0). You can walk back and forth between rooms freely. Return if and only if you can enter every room.
